        <h3 class="wiki-nav-item pb-2" id="uclogic-supported-undetected">
            Supported tablet not detected
        </h3>
        <div class="ms-3">
            <p>
                This is most commonly the result of manufacturer driver leftovers.<br/>
            </p>
            <ol>
                <li>
                    Uninstall any tablet drivers that are currently installed.<br/>
                    <em class="ms-3 text-danger">
                        Deleting files is not a proper method to uninstall drivers,
                        <strong>it will cause issues</strong>.
                        Use the <strong>Settings</strong> app or <strong>Control Panel</strong> instead.
                    </em>
                </li>
                <li>
                    Use the <a href="https://github.com/X9VoiD/WinUSBCleanup/releases/latest">WinUSBCleanup</a>
                    script to automatically clean up any leftovers that uninstallers failed to clean up.
                </li>
            </ol>
        </div>

        <hr/>

        <h3 class="wiki-nav-item pb-2" id="map-raw-input">
            Input does not work in osu!
        </h3>
        <div class="ms-3">
            <p>
                OpenTabletDriver uses the Windows SendInput API to position the cursor from user level permissions.<br/>
                It does not move the cursor in a method that raw input accepts as standard cursor movement.
            </p>
            <ol>
                <li>Disable <code>Map raw input to osu! window</code> in the ingame settings.</li>
            </ol>
        </div>
    </div>
